      "content": "okay, i'm looking at the month-over-month breakdown right now and the revenue actually dipped 15% last month. that doesn't really look like \"consistent churn\" or \"stabilization\" to me, it looks like a pretty significant drop. \n\nif Sequoia's due diligence team sees that cliff in the monthly data, it's going to kill the deal. how are we going to frame this in the deck so it doesn't look like we're losing momentum? can we mask the dip by focusing on a different metric or just present the quarterly average instead?",
